sights.name: Bogotá Botanical Garden
sights.quote: Opened in 1955, this 20-acre botanical park features a waterfall, a sun clock & numerous orchids.

sights.name: Museo Botero
sights.quote: Prominent museum in a colonial mansion featuring works by Fernando Botero & other global artists.

sights.name: Simón Bolívar Metropolitan Park
sights.quote: Large, busy city green space with a walking/biking path, a lake for boating & a kids' playground.

sights.name: Museo Nacional de Colombia
sights.quote: Large museum with 20,000+ artifacts from the 16th century to modern times, plus a restaurant & shop.

sights.name: Gold Museum
sights.quote: Contemporary structure housing exhibits on pre-Columbian gold, ceramics & stones, with a cafe.

sights.name: Usaquén Park
sights.quote: Compact park in a stylish neighborhood known for its arty boutiques, markets & restaurants.

sights.name: Bolivar Square
sights.quote: Spacious city center surrounded by a cathedral & important buildings with notable architecture.

sights.name: Paloquemao
sights.quote: Large local farmer's market with an indoor hall selling fruit, vegetables, meat, fish & flowers.

sights.name: Usaquén Flea Market
sights.quote: Bustling weekly gathering of outdoor vendors selling arts, crafts, food & gifts, plus entertainment.
sights.address: Calle 119 Con Carrera 6a, Bogotá, Cundinamarca, Colombia

sights.name: Salitre Mágico
sights.quote: Amusement park with high-speed roller coasters & go-karts, plus kiddie rides & family attractions.

sights.name: Santuario Nuestra Señora de El Carmen
sights.orig_name: Santuario Nuestra Señora de El Carmen
sights.quote: Florentine Gothic Catholic temple from the early 20th century with a unique striped paint scheme.

html_attributions: Made on the Stree By F. M.

sights.name: Iglesia de San Francisco
sights.quote: Landmark 16th-century Catholic church with an ornate altar & elaborate religious artwork.
sights.address: Av. Jimenez De Quesada #7-10, Bogotá, Colombia

sights.name: Santa Clara Museum
sights.quote: Built in the 17th century, this former church is now a museum, its walls covered in paintings.

sights.name: Parque Mundo Aventura

sights.name: Parque del Chicó
sights.quote: Ceramics, glassware, textiles & religious paintings displayed in a colonial hacienda with a chapel.

sights.name: Military Museum of Colombia
sights.quote: Colombian military museum in a mansion with 9 rooms of historical exhibits & 2 courtyards.

sights.name: Plazoleta Chorro de Quevedo
sights.quote: Historic square featuring a modest fountain, colonial buildings, cafes, restaurants & more.

sights.name: Multiparque
sights.quote: Sizable venue with go-karts, amusement rides, inflatable play areas & other whimsical attractions.

sights.name: House - Museum Quinta Bolívar

sights.name: National Capitol

sights.name: Quebrada La Vieja

sights.orig_name: Palace Historical Museum of the National Police

sights.name: Santuario de Monserrate
